            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AA">
                <p>Publius Nonius Livius Anterotianus, our flamen of the divine Hadrian, is also honoured in <ref target="EmpWor000125.xml">EmpWor00125</ref>.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>To Publius Nonius Livius, son of Publius, of the tribe Palatine, honoured with the public horse by the Imperator Marcus Aurelius Antoninus Augustus, adlected into the decurions by decree of the decurions, flamen of the divine Hadrian, salius of Laurentes and Lavinates, aedile, praetor of the sacred rites of Vulcan. Titus Tinucius Sosiphanes (built this) for his most beloved (and) most pious one. This location was publicly given by decree of the decurions.</p> 
            </div>
